<blockquote>
<p>This is centered around an anomalous community in modern Japan, but also mentions IJAMEA in its pre-history. In it I tried (and am trying) to justify co-existence of IJAMEA, Shūshū-In (JP GoI, an anomalous agency of Imperial Japan) and Yōkai batallion.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Ah yes, I believe I have seen it once while browsing the sandbox. Good to hear from you.</p>
<p>Perhaps we can coordinate ourselves and figure out how everything works out.</p>
<ul>
<li>Onmyo Bureau/Holy Emperor's Council (merged with others to become Foundation)</li>
<li>IJAMEA (dissolved after WWII)</li>
<li>Shushu-in (lasted until 1945)</li>
<li>Unit Negative Numbers (refer to spoilers)</li>
</ul>
<p>Perhaps Negative Numbers is a private project of the Army. As for Shushu-in, how were they during World War II? Forced to assist Japan? Neutral?</p>

