				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/fumeinadebaisu" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2831477); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2831477&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610183506" alt="fumeinadebaisu" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2831477)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/fumeinadebaisu" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2831477); return false;" >fumeinadebaisu</a></span> <span class="odate time_1493908978 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">04 May 2017 14:42</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2810725">
									

<p>Sure. To begin with, gathered some reference for Shushu-In and related groups in the JP articles and forum posts. (note: Shushu-In has many more articles other than these, mostly just with the description like 'once Shushu-In had this, later the Foundation succeeded to.')</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">domestic&nbsp;survey&nbsp;report</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p><a href="http://ja.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-2035180">http://ja.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-2035180</a><br />
A thread of Shushu-In posted in Dec 2016 with links to past similar threads. While there's no concerted predecessor, some users shared an interesting idea about Sen no Rikyu? being the mastermind of the earliest period Shushu-In.</p>
<p><a href="http://ja.scp-wiki.net/kwana-1">http://ja.scp-wiki.net/kwana-1</a><br />
<a href="http://ja.scp-wiki.net/hal-aki-s-proposal">http://ja.scp-wiki.net/hal-aki-s-proposal</a><br />
Shushu-In as an organization that is alternative of the Foundation in a magic-based world.</p>
<p><a href="http://ja.scp-wiki.net/collected-item-no19316">http://ja.scp-wiki.net/collected-item-no19316</a><br />
Shushu-In containing the Foundation by a magical mean.</p>
<p><a href="http://ja.scp-wiki.net/hirose-tale02">http://ja.scp-wiki.net/hirose-tale02</a><br />
Shushu-In, presumably at an alternative universe, communicating (and getting polluted) with yet another universe. Also this document was recovered when the Foundation raided a branch of a GoI which was considered to have some relation with Shushu-In, so it's spanning three universes.</p>
<p><a href="http://ja.scp-wiki.net/seafield13-1">http://ja.scp-wiki.net/seafield13-1</a><br />
<a href="http://ja.scp-wiki.net/kte-3317-green-sunset">http://ja.scp-wiki.net/kte-3317-green-sunset</a><br />
<a href="http://ja.scp-wiki.net/tonannotubasa">http://ja.scp-wiki.net/tonannotubasa</a><br />
Jushich Mikawa, an ex-IJA major and the leader of Mikawa Kikan that was the IJA's pipe with Shushu-In. Visit Europe to receive objects from Axis countries after their surrender, and went missing. Recently reappeared as a leader of an far-right group with his name. Thought as became some kind of reality-bender post-war, GOC designates him as KTE-3317 Green Sunset.</p>
<p><a href="http://ja.scp-wiki.net/2th-goi-contest-hub10">http://ja.scp-wiki.net/2th-goi-contest-hub10</a><br />
<a href="http://ja.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-1270849">http://ja.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-1270849</a><br />
Minor GoIs partly originating from Shushu-In and born post-war.</p>
<p><a href="http://ja.scp-wiki.net/goc-far-east-orientation">http://ja.scp-wiki.net/goc-far-east-orientation</a><br />
五行結社 (Gogyo-Kessha, Five Elements Association), originates from a faction of Onmyoryo and became member of the Council of 108. Known as extremely hostile to Unit Negative Numbers.</p>
<p><a href="http://ja.scp-wiki.net/scp-1912-jp">http://ja.scp-wiki.net/scp-1912-jp</a><br />
Mentions cooperation with the Foundation in 1930 and 'marge in 1945 after collaborative relationship.' Also, there's an Esoterica Department in the Foundation.</p>
<p><a href="http://ja.scp-wiki.net/scp-1200-jp">http://ja.scp-wiki.net/scp-1200-jp</a><br />
In the last days of the war, Shushu-In cooperated with The Supreme War Council to protect Kyoto from war damage, as 70% of Mainland objects they collected was contained there. This effort ended up exploiting a reality-bending entity to transfer a nuclear bomb to an extradimensional realm, eventually neutralizing the entity.</p>
<p><a href="http://ja.scp-wiki.net/seafield13-tale-2-2">http://ja.scp-wiki.net/seafield13-tale-2-2</a><br />
An obscure staff is being asked to translate 'Secure, Contain, Protect' to Japanese. Mentions the upper echelons ignoring approaches from the Foundation before the surrender.</p>
<p>Other recurrent and/or fragmented settings:</p>
<ul>
<li>Other than 研儀官 (higikan, mystagogue; a researcher without any meaningful thaumaturgic power, or a staff who does paperwork or bureaucratic tasks) and 秘儀官 (higikan, mystic), there are several kin groups specialized as physical assault force(s) or espionage unit(s) doing such jobs as traditional family businesses, usually called 刀 (katana).</li>
<li>Some ex-Shushu-In members with anomalous properties, possibly stemming from the UNN 'super soldier' project and many of them have anomalies of de facto immortality or rejuvenation, are employed by the Foundation.</li>
<li>Recently a KO user made inquiry at the JP forum about the idea of North Korea GoI which has had recovered anomalies UNN had left in the Korean Peninsula when they had gone back to Mainland Japan after the war. The answer was that Ashifune has surrendered almost every remaining anomaly he gathered for UNN to the Foundation.</li>
</ul>
<p>And there are some more minor GoIs from the alternative universe(s) and possibly have something to do with the Axis powers too.</p>
<p><a href="http://ja.scp-wiki.net/sadahiko-s-homepage-html">http://ja.scp-wiki.net/sadahiko-s-homepage-html</a><br />
<a href="http://ja.scp-wiki.net/system:page-tags/tag/%E8%89%A6%E9%9A%8A#pages">http://ja.scp-wiki.net/system:page-tags/tag/%E8%89%A6%E9%9A%8A#pages</a></p>
<p>艦隊 (Kantai, the Fleet) consists of ships from various ages/backgrounds, perhaps including IJN. 幻島同盟 (The Confederate Island Countries of Phantom) consists of phantom islands and legendary lands. It sees Kantai as a hostile group, and refers to <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thule" target="_blank">Thule</a> as an ever-mysterious place/group.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>In EN, <a href="/scp-824">SCP-824</a> was initially discovered in 'an extradimensional, self-contained region accessible from a point in southern China,' and later in a small community in Japan where residents 'have not been cooperative with Foundation personnel, and generally react with suspicion to inquiries about or studies of SCP-824-1,' with records from 1937. And <a href="/scp-2928">SCP-2928</a> made my headcanon that Shushu-In was skillful at anti-memetics.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>As for Shushu-in, how were they during World War II? Forced to assist Japan? Neutral?</p>
</blockquote>
<p>In the case of SCP-1200-JP, it seems to me that it's implying Shushu-In was reluctant about other form of collaboration. If Kyoto had been blown up, there would have been XK-senario in that plot. So cooperation may be for the sake of protection of normalcy, not (only) for the Empire. It also seems like, for some reason, they couldn't take proactive means to fend off attacks rather than waiting for the airplanes to come. Apart from this, Shushu-In being relatively free from the Imperial Japanese government seems rather popular as a headcanon.</p>
<p>P.S. Piercing together those information, I think here we got some neat idea to get a few things work well. For example, how to survive in a post-war world in the form of paramilitary groups such as IJAMEA:</p>
<ul>
<li>Utilizing anomalous spaces, just like Yokai Yokocho, as shelters and/or secret HQs.</li>
<li>Hiding in remote and low-level population areas, as of SCP-824-1.</li>
<li>Hiding entrances for hideouts, hideouts themselves, or personnel with anti-memetic technology.</li>
</ul>

							</div>

								
					
